rsQueueMIB.name: rsQueueMIB
rsQueueMIB.contactinfo: Riverstone Networks Customer Service Postal: Riverstone Networks, Inc 5200 Great America Parkway Santa Clara CA 95054 USA PHONE:+1 408.878.6500 EMAIL: nms-eng@riverstonenet.com WEB: http://www.riverstonenet.com
rsQueueMIB.description: This MIB module represents information on each of the queues for each port.

IndexInteger.name: IndexInteger
IndexInteger.description: An integer which may be used as a table index.

rsQueuePropertiesTable.name: rsQueuePropertiesTable
rsQueuePropertiesTable.description: This table contains descriptions of different queues. It is used as a reference table by rsQueueStatsTable.

rsQueuePropertiesEntry.name: rsQueuePropertiesEntry
rsQueuePropertiesEntry.description: This entry represents a queue and its properties. It is indexed by a natural number.

rsQueueId.name: rsQueueId
rsQueueId.description: An index that enumerates the number of queue entries.

rsQueueName.name: rsQueueName
rsQueueName.description: The name of the queue. For example, on the RS platform, the four queue names are control, high, medium, and low.

rsQueueDescr.name: rsQueueDescr
rsQueueDescr.description: A more detailed description of the functionality of the queue.

rsQueueDiscardPolicy.name: rsQueueDiscardPolicy
rsQueueDiscardPolicy.description: The type of policy used by the queue to drop a frame.

rsQueueMaxCapacity.name: rsQueueMaxCapacity
rsQueueMaxCapacity.description: The max number of frames the queue can contain.

rsQueueStatsTable.name: rsQueueStatsTable
rsQueueStatsTable.description: This table contains stats per queue for each physical interface.

rsQueueStatsEntry.name: rsQueueStatsEntry
rsQueueStatsEntry.description: The stats per queue for each physical interface.

rsQueueStatsLastCapChange.name: rsQueueStatsLastCapChange
rsQueueStatsLastCapChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the port capability changed. As a result of this change, the application need to restart its counter collection. For example, the card may have been hotswapped out and replaced by another card.

rsQueueStatsValid.name: rsQueueStatsValid
rsQueueStatsValid.description: The current state of each counter in this table. Each bit indicate the validity of a counter. Some queues may not support every counter in the table.

rsQueueBytes.name: rsQueueBytes
rsQueueBytes.description: The number of bytes that have passed through this priority queue on this port.

rsQueueFrames.name: rsQueueFrames
rsQueueFrames.description: The number of frames that have passed through this priority queue on this port.

rsQueueDiscards.name: rsQueueDiscards
rsQueueDiscards.description: The number of frames into this queue that were discarded because the queue was full.

rsQueueHCBytes.name: rsQueueHCBytes
rsQueueHCBytes.description: The number of bytes stored in a 64 bit counter that have passed through this priority queue on this port.

rsQueueHCFrames.name: rsQueueHCFrames
rsQueueHCFrames.description: The number of frames stored in a 64 bit counter that have passed through this priority queue on this port.

rsQueuePropertiesGroup.name: rsQueuePropertiesGroup
rsQueuePropertiesGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent properties of a queue.

rsQueueStatsGroup.name: rsQueueStatsGroup
rsQueueStatsGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent the queue stats.
